This paper presents a temporal model for reasoning on disjunctive metric constraints on intervals and time points in temporal contexts. The paper focuses on the development of a labeled temporal algebra and its reasoning algorithms, which can manage labeled constraints, associated label lists, and sets of mutually inconsistent disjuncts. The paper also discusses the organization of constraints in a hierarchy of alternative temporal contexts and the representation of non-binary constraints. Based on these characteristics, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), as the paper deals with reasoning algorithms and logical dependencies. Additionally, the paper involves the use of data structures and algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper discusses the representation of constraints, which could be relevant to cs.DB (Databases).
